			&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;h1 id="deploy"&gt;Deploy&lt;/h1&gt;

		&lt;/li&gt;
	
		&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;
				&lt;a href="/2020/09/25/Consideracoes_finais.html"&gt;Consideracoes_finais&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;h1 id="considerações-finais"&gt;Considerações finais&lt;/h1&gt;

		&lt;/li&gt;
	
		&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;
				&lt;a href="/2020/09/25/Colecoes.html"&gt;Colecoes&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;h1 id="coleções"&gt;Coleções&lt;/h1&gt;

		&lt;/li&gt;
	
		&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;
				&lt;a href="/2020/09/25/Blogging.html"&gt;Blogging&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;h1 id="blogging"&gt;Blogging&lt;/h1&gt;

		&lt;/li&gt;
	
		&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;
				&lt;a href="/2020/09/25/Assets.html"&gt;Assets&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;h1 id="assets"&gt;Assets&lt;/h1&gt;

		&lt;/li&gt;
	
		&lt;li&gt;
			&lt;h2&gt;
				&lt;a href="/2020/09/25/Arquivos_de_dados.html"&gt;Arquivos_de_dados&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/h2&gt;
			&lt;h1 id="arquivos-de-dados"&gt;Arquivos de dados&lt;/h1&gt;

		&lt;/li&gt;
	
</span><span class="nt">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Explicando o que ocorre neste arquivo (o que entendi) primeiramente herdamos o default, damos o titulo da pagina de blog, entre as tags &lt;ul&gt; e &lt;/ul&gt; criamos um for que verificará todos arquivos na pasta posts e entre as tags &lt;h2&gt; e &lt;/h2&gt; inserimos um link que pegará o arquivo na url e o seguinte pega o title do post. A  pega o primeiro paragrafo do conteudo do post (pelo que entendi). Também vamos colocar o link para o arquivo blog.html no arquivo de navegação do yml em _data/navigation.yml e ficará com dado abaixo.</p>

<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="p">-</span> name: Home
  link: /
<span class="p">-</span> name: About
  link: /about.html
<span class="p">-</span> name: Blog
  link: /blog.html
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>E então para verificar vamos criar mais post em nosso blog para verificar a navegação… Para não ter que traduzir os textos vou copiar e colar o texto do tutorial. E no nome do arquivo colocarei datas anteriores.</p>

<p>Arquivo data 2020-09-24-macans.md</p>

<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nn">---</span>
<span class="na">layout</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">post</span>
<span class="na">author</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">jill</span>
<span class="nn">---</span>
An apple is a sweet, edible fruit produced by an apple tree.

Apple trees are cultivated worldwide, and are the most widely grown species in
the genus Malus. The tree originated in Central Asia, where its wild ancestor,
Malus sieversii, is still found today. Apples have been grown for thousands of
years in Asia and Europe, and were brought to North America by European
colonists.
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Arquivo data <strong>2020-09-23-kiwi.md</strong></p>

<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nn">---</span>
<span class="na">layout</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">post</span>
<span class="na">author</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">ted</span>
<span class="nn">---</span>
Kiwifruit (often abbreviated as kiwi), or Chinese gooseberry is the edible
berry of several species of woody vines in the genus Actinidia.

The most common cultivar group of kiwifruit is oval, about the size of a large
hen's egg (5–8 cm (2.0–3.1 in) in length and 4.5–5.5 cm (1.8–2.2 in) in
diameter). It has a fibrous, dull greenish-brown skin and bright green or
golden flesh with rows of tiny, black, edible seeds. The fruit has a soft
texture, with a sweet and unique flavor.
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>E pronto, vamos verificar nosso blog.</p>
